1.title: Mediterranean Oasis
1.plot: Allen and Lily's uninviting yard is haggard and ignored, so Matt comes to their rescue with a Mediterranean oasis design. They want a place to hang out with friends and family, so Matt gives them a large deck complete with a barbecue island and a reclaimed dining table. He also adds an amazing stone water and fire feature as the center point, then builds a paver patio adjacent to it as well as a custom day bed with a pergola.

2.title: Rock Pond Space Living
2.plot: Matt Blashaw transforms a dirt pile of a backyard with an old shed and dying plants into an entertainer's dream with the addition of a cascading rock pond, huge paver patio, reclaimed wood BBQ cooking station and games.

3.title: Hamptons Hangout
3.plot: Homeowners avoid spending time in their dark, uninviting yard until Matt Blashaw delivers a design they can't resist. He installs a multi-tiered deck, a concrete paver patio with a fire pit and a custom wood and steel bar.

4.title: Modern Party Pad
4.plot: What was once just a barren deck and dirt landscape gets a shade structure, steel water feature, living wall and bocce court. Matt Blashaw adds lush green plants and a custom metal fire feature to create one inviting party pad.

5.title: Kansas City English Garden
5.plot: Sophie's soggy, sloping yard needs help, so she pleads for Matt Blashaw to come home with her. He designs a usable space for grilling, dining and lounging, all with an English garden vibe. He also fixes a few problems he encounters along the way, like installing a few retaining walls to level the space, adding drainage to move the water away and raising and reinforcing the deck posts. Finally, Matt adds a staircase for access and a composting area to give Sophie the ultimate outdoor space.

6.title: Kansas City Outdoor Room
6.plot: A small, hot backyard with a rotten deck is transformed into a quaint outdoor living room. The team installs a brand new deck along with a pergola, privacy screens and a custom outdoor sofa with a built-in ice chest.

7.title: Beer Garden Backyard
7.plot: Matt Blashaw transforms a small and cluttered backyard into a beer garden fit for a home brewer. Giant concrete pavers clean up what was once a mess, and a built-in barbecue and custom bar bring an industrial tap to center stage.

8.title: Contemporary Elegance
8.plot: Juan and Katy's expansive, empty yard doesn't give them enough living space to eat, cook and entertain. Matt Blashaw steps in and adds a huge gravel patio as well as a modern pergola with room for dining and lounging areas.

9.title: Modern Zen Backyard
9.plot: Matt Blashaw and his crew turn a barren yard into a Zen oasis by building floating decks that wrap around three reflecting pools. A pergola creates shade, and a redwood counter is the centerpiece of a new grilling area.

10.title: Tiki Bar Backyard
10.plot: Matt Blashaw and his crew transform a cluttered backyard into a modern space with a water and fire feature. They replace broken patio furniture and uneven pavers with a custom outdoor kitchen, rolling tiki bar and high-top table.

11.title: Brick Bar Backyard
11.plot: A small backyard is transformed into an entertainer's dream. The lone tree is removed to make way for a large deck with built-in seating and a fire pit. A brick bar and a pizza oven make this backyard the ultimate party space!

12.title: Funky Hammock Deck
12.plot: An Orange County backyard with zero purpose and tons of weeds is transformed into the ultimate hangout with a custom hammock sofa, water feature and two-tiered deck with a barbecue smoker.

13.title: Industrial-Modern in the OC
13.plot: Back in his hometown of Orange County, CA, Matt Blashaw and his crew transform the small backyard of a fixer-upper into an industrial-modern retreat complete with inviting dining area, barbecue island and custom lounge chairs.

7.title: Tampa Party Pad
7.plot: A Tampa couple has no entertainment space, just grass on a sloping, uneven backyard. This backyard makeover consists of two thick paver patio areas. The top level has an outdoor bar made of polymer cabinets topped with granite and illuminated by different flashing colored LED lights. It also has a 40-inch TV built in. Adjacent to the bar are four grand water fountains underneath a decorative wood arbor. Then, step down on to a flagstone pathway leading to the lower level patio with a central fire feature adorned by three fire bowl columns.

Surrounding the fire pit are custom-made campfire roasting forks. This large space transforms to an entertainment, eating and relaxing area for the whole family.

1.plot: Matt Blashaw and the team head to Blog Cabin in North Carolina to help transform the massive waterfront property into a cozy entertaining area. He builds a solid covered pergola with a paver patio that provides a hangout area.

2.plot: A lackluster yard turns into a tranquil contemporary oasis.

3.title: Shady Oasis

4.title: Wine Barrel Haven
4.plot: The owners' love of wine barrels inspires Matt to transform their backyard into an outdoor kitchen with a hanging wine barrel light and shaded patio.

5.title: Contemporary Grids

3.title: Old World Hideaway
3.plot: Chris and his team give a blank-slate backyard an old world makeover, including a redwood deck and stone fireplace.

4.title: Blog Cabin Lakeview Living
4.plot: Chris goes to Idaho to transform an upper deck and front yard into a mountain retreat with lake views.

5.title: Yard Crashers Visits Blog Cabin
5.plot: Chris goes to Blog Cabin in North Carolina to transform a waterfront property into an entertaining area with pergola.

6.title: TheTan, Chill and Grill Yard
6.plot: Chris and his team turn a big blank slate of a backyard into a Tuscan-inspired outdoor living space for a party-loving couple.

7.title: Modern Bamboo Haven
7.plot: Chris and his crew transform a dilapidated backyard into a modern bamboo haven.

8.title: West Coast Party Pad
8.plot: Chris and his crew crash a boring, neglected yard and transform it into a West Coast party pad.

9.title: Contemporary Shade Yard
9.plot: Chris helps Ian and Katie transform a boring uninviting yard into a entertaining area with a shaded pergola, fire pit and L-shaped seating.

10.title: Eclectic Cottage
10.plot: With the help of Chris and his team, this boring backyard is transformed into a splashy Spanish Courtyard with colorful metal art, a custom pub bar table and a relaxing lounge area.

11.title: Spanish Courtyard
11.plot: With the help of Chris and his team, this boring backyard is transformed into a splashy Spanish Courtyard with colorful metal art, a custom pub bar table and a relaxing lounge area.

12.title: Nautical Cape Cod
12.plot: Chris crashes a plain Cape Cod backyard and transforms it into a nautical-inspired entertaining space complete with a built-in barbecue, wood plank bar, flagstone patio and fire pit.

13.title: Pacific Coast Rustic Loggia
13.plot: A desperate backyard in disrepair turns into a rustic sports lounge with a three-sided loggia, kegorator and oversized fire pit.

1.title: Contemporary Cedar Design
1.plot: Chris and the crew crash a dysfunctional space with a tiny pink patio and no entertaining area. They transform the yard into a private party pad complete with a cedar slat pergola, custom dining table and a matching bar.

2.title: Rustic Farm Backyard
2.plot: This backyard has gone to the chickens and these homeowners desperately want to co-exist with their critters. Chris delivers a design with an oversized chicken coop, water wheel, a 10-foot farm table and a rustic grill island.

3.title: Tranquil Retreat
3.plot: Chris crashes TJ and Julie's backyard, a sad space with a small patio and no landscaping. The crew adds a huge paver patio with a dining table, a built-in barbecue island and a tranquil water feature.

4.title: Urban Putting Green Yard
4.plot: Chris Lambton and his crew turn a neglected, overgrown yard into an urban putting green with a redwood deck, a custom prep counter, charcoal stone pathways and a rustic water feature.

5.title: Outdoor Living Room
5.plot: Chris Lambton and his crew transform a dilapidated yard into a massive outdoor room, including an oversized bamboo deck, a custom bar made from wine barrels and a living wall full of colorful plants.

6.title: Urban Wine Barrel Bar
6.plot: Chris Lambton and his crew transform a dilapidated yard into a massive outdoor room, including an oversized bamboo deck, a custom bar made from wine barrels and a living wall full of colorful plants.

7.title: Mid-Century Modern Revival
7.plot: A couple's original 1950s backyard desperately needs to be updated. Chris transforms it into a private midcentury modern entertaining mecca with a monkey pod fire feature, barbecue area with prep space and a large dining area.

9.title: San Diego Beachy Backyard
9.plot: Brent and Mariah's backyard concrete jungle needs help! Chris delivers a beach-y San Diego vibe that's perfect for entertaining, complete with a colored concrete patio, redwood pergola, custom dining table and a surfboard bar.

10.title: Charleston Low Country Escape
10.plot: A couple's flood-prone yard is rotting, so they beg Chris for an outdoor living room suited to low-country style entertaining. He creates a huge outdoor kitchen and bar with a new smoker, a hanging daybed and raised patio.

11.title: Traditional Charleston Courtyard
11.plot: Chris and his crew transform a dull, muddy space into a traditional Charleston backyard. They install a local hand-cut brick patio, an oyster fire pit, a reclaimed farmhouse table and a Charleston arbor to welcome guests.

12.title: Lower Lounge at Blog Cabin
12.plot: Chris and his team head to Blog Cabin 2016 to transform an unused area under the stilted house into a lower lounge that capitalizes on the gulf view.

13.title: Sky Cabin Side Yard at Blog Cabin
13.plot: Chris and his team descend on Blog Cabin 2016 to turn an empty side yard into a recreational area complete with a stilted guest retreat and a sand volleyball court.

-1.title: Hillside Party Hot Tub
-1.plot: Chris Lambton transforms a backyard wasteland into a hillside party pad. Features include a redwood upper deck with a bubbling hot tub and a lower patio area with plenty of space to hang out. A massive new grill finishes it off!

plot: Experienced DIY Matt Blashaw fixes up people's backyards for free in just three days.
